Inline-block display combines features of both inline and block elements. 
Inline-block elements can appear next to each other and we can specify 
their dimensions using the width and height properties.


<div class="rectangle">
  <p>Iâ€™m a rectangle!</p>
</div>
<div class="rectangle">
  <p>So am I!</p>
</div>
<div class="rectangle">
  <p>Me three!</p>
</div>


.rectangle {
  display: inline-block;
  width: 200px;
  height: 300px;
}


There are three rectangular divs that each contain a paragraph of text lined 
up horizontally.